The paper proposes a generative machine comprehension model that learns to ask and answer questions based on documents. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML), which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as it covers NLP research. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories as they cover ML research. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible category as the paper deals with information seeking. Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper uses a sequence-to-sequence framework that involves neural networks.
